&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;450&quot; data-end=&quot;480&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;457&quot; data-end=&quot;480&quot;&gt;About Genius Sports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;482&quot; data-end=&quot;776&quot;&gt;Genius Sports is a global leader in sports data and technology, powering the ecosystem that connects sports, betting, and media. With over 20 years of experience and a network of more than 500 sports league partnerships, Genius Sports delivers cutting-edge solutions across five core divisions.&amp;nbsp;With offices across the globe, Genius Sports supports live operations that fuel the digital transformation of sport.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;482&quot; data-end=&quot;776&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note: Please submit your CV in English.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an &lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;On-site Tracking Hardware Support (OTHS)&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be the first line of support for Genius Sports’ hardware infrastructure at sports venues. Your mission is to maintain, troubleshoot, and ensure the correct operation of the Dragon tracking systems and video streaming hardware used in elite stadiums.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a key point of contact on-site, working independently or with remote support from engineering teams, ensuring our equipment functions correctly before and during live sports events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;p-rich_text_list p-rich_text_list__bullet p-rich_text_list--nested&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;unordered-list&quot; data-list-tree=&quot;true&quot; data-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Serve as the first responder for hardware and connectivity issues in stadiums (MD and MD-1 support).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Perform basic troubleshooting and maintenance:
&lt;ul class=&quot;p-rich_text_list p-rich_text_list__bullet p-rich_text_list--nested&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;unordered-list&quot; data-list-tree=&quot;true&quot; data-indent=&quot;1&quot; data-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;1&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Reseat, replace, or terminate copper and fibre cables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;1&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Power cycle/reboot network devices (servers, switches, routers)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;1&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Clean, re-angle, and reposition cameras as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Connect to networking equipment via laptop for diagnostics (with remote engineering support)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Replace hardware components (e.g., cameras, cables, connectors) with provided equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Document actions and issues post-visit via internal reporting systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Coordinate with stadium staff and remote support teams in a professional manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Use ladders and access elevated or restricted areas to maintain or inspect equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Be on call for urgent match-day (-1) support when required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;

